rComments: best prof ever, love him!

Extremely clear and well organized lectures with good slides. Funny guy who really drives the main point home. He taught POL101 with Prof Kopstein and they had a great dynamic together, balanced each other out. Definitely a great class where I was able to learn a lot.
love him
Prof Wong was not only knowledgeable, but helpful and clear. He inspires conversation and respects every student's opinion. I highly recommend taking a course with him.

Professor Wong is very intellectual. He knows the material he is teaching inside out, evident from the way he discusses it and when he answers any student questions. First years, his lectures are long and apparently monotone (who cares) but in the upper years you'll realize what a clear cut and insightful instructor Professor Wong was.
Professor Wong in his lectures sometimes gets a bit monotone but they still remain interesting. He's very approachable and a down to earth guy. Definitely my favourite class first year.
great prof! knows what he's talking about and really makes you think about what you're learning.

Wong is a great prof.  His lectures are really detailed, and he breaks down the material so everything is clear and understood.  He's witty and incorporates interesting experiences into his lectures, which makes them more interesting.  Overall great guy with an effective lecturing style.
Professor Wong is my favorite Professor! I really enjoy this class and his topics !
Magnificent lecture on Taiwan. Passion. Charismatic, intelligent. Awesomeeee!
Thanks for the great lecture Dr. Wong! Crystal as usual. Loved it.

If it's hard to understand, maybe then POL is not your cup of tea. Wait till you get to 2nd, 3rd year bud. I consider Wong/Kopstein as top profs in here. As to articles, except for Evans, I got it all. So what there is no book? You saved a $100).

This course is taught by Mr. Wong and Mr. Kopstein. They do not upload powerpoints online. There is no textbook. The readings are on blackboard, and the readings are lengthy and difficult to understand.
Dr. Wong is a very interesting lecturer. You'll never sleep there. He finishes early and talk is direct and useful.

This is a split class prof wise, which in this case actually works as both have specific areas of interest in what is a fairly broad intro course. Lectures are important to the pace of the material and Wong asks questions rather than giving all the answers - very important. His lectures usefully informative on East Asian development and politics.

I had Wong along with Kopstein for POL101. Wong doesn't stand out much to me as a professor, other than his lectures were very organized. VERY important to do your readings in this course. The readings were incredibly heavy for a 100-level class, which may be the only con.

Wong was interesting, to the point and witty. Easy to follow. Listen carefully and he details what is expected in the essays and the exams.  My TA said that the profs were not very imaginative when it came to the exams and she was right. Look at the old exams for your revision, you wont go wrong - especially for the multiple choice!
Superb orator. Concepts are clearly explained in a fluid fashion that allows for great note-taking. Lectures are very interesting. Great guy.

Not as interesting as the other prof who teaches this course, but more clear and organized lecture-wise. Can be witty sometimes. Explains concepts well. Manages to tie East Asia into every example ever. All in all, good prof, great course.
I love this course because it forces you to learn something useful. In other words, The prof. make political science101 memorable.

Great prof! I preferred him over Kopstein. Lectures were crystal clear and easy to follow. Wong is articulate and funny, not to mention approachable, summarizes effectively, and uses real-world examples. Tests are no surprise. My interest in the course at the beginning was pretty low but I'm actually planning on majoring in it thanks to POL101!
Professor Wong is a sick dude. He's not as funny as Kopstein (the other prof for my course), but his content is a bit more interesting. He does always talk about Asia, but its always interesting
He's clear and interesting. I find him a better lecturer than the other professor who teaches this course. He's easy to listen to and quite good at explaining things. Rather funny too.

a little boring, but helpful. talks about China every class. on the first day we had a person pass out on the floor and he did nothing. tried to talk as normal. other prof stoped him. overall he is OK.
One of the most articulate  professors I have had. His arguments are far more sophisticated than the other professor who teaches this course. Fairly easy but interesting introductory survey course.
Good lecturer, unfortunately a totally useless class that was far too broad. Dumbed down his lectures way too much.

I really great lecturer and made really complex topics easy to understand.  His lectures were very organized and made note-taking a breeze.  He provided tons of examples which were very useful for the essays and final exam.
Manages to tie Hong Kong into every lecture. Every example is about China.
His lectures were very engaging and interesting.  At the end of each lecture he summarizes his points.  I preferred him over Kopstein
Single handedly the most effective teacher from my experience. The best professor that I've ever had, and probably will ever have.
Incredibly useful course.  Great Professor.
Good professor, knows the material well. I did not learn that much in the course though - it all made sense when he summarized the discussion, but this was not always done
His course is disorganized and dated.  He is also very self important.
Young, unapologetic and arrogant! Nothing less, nothing more!

He does not fell the need to bother with undergraduates students who have not completed prior research for or under him.  Extends deadlines for certain individuals, while deducting 5% a day off of the assignments of other students.  He is rude, arrogant and although “bright”, should not be teaching anyone, in any course, at any level.  Good luck to
Not a very good prof!!! Incapable of giving any student a decent mark (those that deserve it of course)!
Great lecturer, insightful, brilliant and funny. He has high standards and expectations but is well worth the effort.
No Comments
SO much fun
Great prof.  Brings to light many ethical and moral issues, provacative.  Friendly, personable.
Great discussion leader and very insightful
Expects a lot, but is very approachable, has extremely insightful lectures, welcomes feedback, grades fairly, and is funny.  The best prof I've had.
brutal
Terrible marking of assignments, too much reading, unjustified means of calculating class participation.
No Comments
ARTICULATE, FUNNY, INSIGHTFUL AND PROVOCATIVE... AND HE CAN REMEMBER NAMES
The course is tough but well worth it. He is smart, articulate and approachable.
Can't answer questions, or recognize a student after many office visits-horrible
